Reasoning: I attempted to run unit tests (sample and randomized cases) with an automated test harness, but the execution environment lacked a Python interpreter so the tests could not be executed. By static analysis the algorithm is functionally correct: it enumerates allowed remainders for each digit and searches for three distinct congruent times, so it would pass many small and sample cases. However the implementation generates up to O(M^2) candidate times per reel and examines all triple combinations, yielding a worst-case O(M^6) workload (for example, M=100 with all reels identical), which will cause timeouts on heavy inputs and lowers the correctness and robustness ratings. Style is relatively good due to clear comments and a helper function, but simplicity and maintainability suffer because of the brute-force approach and lack of pruning or early exits.
